{"title":"Trek Marlin+ adds Bosch e-Bike Power to Popular Hardtail","link":"https://bikerumor.com/trek-marlin-plus-e-bike/","date":1707359274000,"content":"<p><img width=\"1900\" height=\"1267\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/trek-marlin-plus-alloy-hardtail-eMTB-2.jpg\" alt=\"trek marlin+ alloy hardtail e-mountain bike being ridden\" loading=\"lazy\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/trek-marlin-plus-alloy-hardtail-eMTB-2.jpg 1900w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/trek-marlin-plus-alloy-hardtail-eMTB-2-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/trek-marlin-plus-alloy-hardtail-eMTB-2-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/trek-marlin-plus-alloy-hardtail-eMTB-2-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/trek-marlin-plus-alloy-hardtail-eMTB-2-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/trek-marlin-plus-alloy-hardtail-eMTB-2-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/trek-marlin-plus-alloy-hardtail-eMTB-2-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></p>\n<p>The new Trek Marlin+ takes their all-purpose alloy hardtail and gives it the Bosch Active Line upgrade. The e-bike variant has all the same features as the analog original, giving you a wide range of use options, from trail to town.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Featuring 2.6″ tires, a 120mm suspension fork, and size-specific wheel selections, the Marlin+ scoots all of that along with a 50Nm mid-mount motor.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1900\" height=\"1267\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/trek-marlin-plus-alloy-hardtail-eMTB-3.jpg\" alt=\"trek marlin+ alloy hardtail e-mountain bike being ridden\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/trek-marlin-plus-alloy-hardtail-eMTB-3.jpg 1900w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/trek-marlin-plus-alloy-hardtail-eMTB-3-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/trek-marlin-plus-alloy-hardtail-eMTB-3-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/trek-marlin-plus-alloy-hardtail-eMTB-3-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/trek-marlin-plus-alloy-hardtail-eMTB-3-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/trek-marlin-plus-alloy-hardtail-eMTB-3-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/trek-marlin-plus-alloy-hardtail-eMTB-3-720x480.jpg 720w\" />\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\n\t\t        <div>\n                \n                    \n                \n                <div>\n<figure><img alt=\"trek marlin+ alloy hardtail e-mountain bike being ridden\" /></figure>\n</div>\n                <div>\n<figure><img alt=\"trek marlin+ alloy hardtail e-mountain bike being ridden\" /></figure>\n</div>\n                <div></div>\n        </div></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>It’s a Class 1 e-bike, assisting up to 20mph or 25km/h, depending on market. A bolt-on cover on the non-drive side makes motor service easy, and a protective plate under it makes cable routing simple.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1900\" height=\"1267\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/trek-marlin-plus-alloy-hardtail-eMTB-4.jpg\" alt=\"external bosch battery pack shown on trek marlin+ alloy hardtail e-mountain bike\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/trek-marlin-plus-alloy-hardtail-eMTB-4.jpg 1900w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/trek-marlin-plus-alloy-hardtail-eMTB-4-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/trek-marlin-plus-alloy-hardtail-eMTB-4-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/trek-marlin-plus-alloy-hardtail-eMTB-4-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/trek-marlin-plus-alloy-hardtail-eMTB-4-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/trek-marlin-plus-alloy-hardtail-eMTB-4-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/trek-marlin-plus-alloy-hardtail-eMTB-4-720x480.jpg 720w\" />\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\n\t\t        <div>\n                \n                    \n                \n                <div>\n<figure><img alt=\"external bosch battery pack shown on trek marlin+ alloy hardtail e-mountain bike\" /></figure>\n</div>\n                <div>\n<figure><img alt=\"external bosch battery pack shown on trek marlin+ alloy hardtail e-mountain bike\" /></figure>\n</div>\n                <div></div>\n        </div></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>That’s paired with a 400Wh CompactTube battery, augmented with an optional 250Wh PowerMore range extender. Expect 2-4 hours of run time on a full charge, and about 50% more than that with the external battery pack. It uses the slim Bosch Purion display/remote for simple mode switches and easy visuals for power, speed, etc. Switch to Auto mode for automatic assist changes based on terrain, cadence, and your output.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1900\" height=\"1267\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/trek-marlin-plus-alloy-hardtail-commuter-bike-.jpg\" alt=\"trek marlin+ alloy hardtail e-mountain bike shown with pannier bags and rack for commuting\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/trek-marlin-plus-alloy-hardtail-commuter-bike-.jpg 1900w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/trek-marlin-plus-alloy-hardtail-commuter-bike--297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/trek-marlin-plus-alloy-hardtail-commuter-bike--800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/trek-marlin-plus-alloy-hardtail-commuter-bike--120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/trek-marlin-plus-alloy-hardtail-commuter-bike--768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/trek-marlin-plus-alloy-hardtail-commuter-bike--1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/trek-marlin-plus-alloy-hardtail-commuter-bike--720x480.jpg 720w\" />\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\n\t\t        <div>\n                \n                    \n                \n                <div>\n<figure><img alt=\"trek marlin+ alloy hardtail e-mountain bike shown with pannier bags and rack for commuting\" /></figure>\n</div>\n                <div>\n<figure><img alt=\"trek marlin+ alloy hardtail e-mountain bike shown with pannier bags and rack for commuting\" /></figure>\n</div>\n                <div></div>\n        </div></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Size medium frames and up get 29″ wheels, small &amp; XS get 27.5″ wheels. All frame sizes get rack and fender mounts, letting you set it up for backroad touring and urban commuting. Or shed the cargo and shred the trail.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Trek Marlin+ Specs &amp; Pricing</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Two builds are available, both on the affordable end of Trek’s e-bike lineup.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2200\" height=\"1650\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/trek-marlin8-alloy-hardtail-eMTB.jpg\" alt=\"trek marlin+ 8 eMTB\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/trek-marlin8-alloy-hardtail-eMTB.jpg 2200w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/trek-marlin8-alloy-hardtail-eMTB-297x223.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/trek-marlin8-alloy-hardtail-eMTB-800x600.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/trek-marlin8-alloy-hardtail-eMTB-120x90.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/trek-marlin8-alloy-hardtail-eMTB-768x576.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/trek-marlin8-alloy-hardtail-eMTB-1536x1152.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/trek-marlin8-alloy-hardtail-eMTB-2048x1536.jpg 2048w\" />\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\n\t\t        <div>\n                \n                    \n                \n                <div>\n<figure><img alt=\"trek marlin+ 8 eMTB\" /></figure>\n</div>\n                <div>\n<figure><img alt=\"trek marlin+ 8 eMTB\" /></figure>\n</div>\n                <div></div>\n        </div></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Marlin+ 8</strong><br />Shimano Deore 12-speed drivetrain, dropper seatpost, Shimano 4 piston hydraulic disc brakes, 120mm RockShox Recon Silver Air fork, Tubeless Ready wheels and Bontrager Gunnison Pro XR 29×2.6” tires. MSRP $3,499. Also available in gray/silver.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2200\" height=\"1650\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/trek-marlin6-alloy-hardtail-eMTB.jpg\" alt=\"trek marlin+ 6 eMTB\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/trek-marlin6-alloy-hardtail-eMTB.jpg 2200w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/trek-marlin6-alloy-hardtail-eMTB-297x223.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/trek-marlin6-alloy-hardtail-eMTB-800x600.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/trek-marlin6-alloy-hardtail-eMTB-120x90.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/trek-marlin6-alloy-hardtail-eMTB-768x576.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/trek-marlin6-alloy-hardtail-eMTB-1536x1152.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/trek-marlin6-alloy-hardtail-eMTB-2048x1536.jpg 2048w\" />\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\n\t\t        <div>\n                \n                    \n                \n                <div>\n<figure><img alt=\"trek marlin+ 6 eMTB\" /></figure>\n</div>\n                <div>\n<figure><img alt=\"trek marlin+ 6 eMTB\" /></figure>\n</div>\n                <div></div>\n        </div></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Marlin+ 6</strong><br />Shimano wide range CUES drivetrain, Shimano Linkglide cassette, Tektro hydraulic brakes with 203mm rotors, 120mm SR Suntour XCM 34 fork, Bontrager Montrose 29”x2.4” tires. MSRP $2,699. Also available in black.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Available now globally in most markets. Prefer the standard version? The analog Trek Marlin <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/trek-upgrades-marlin-mtb/\">got a refresh</a> in 2023.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><em><a href=\"https://www.trekbikes.com/us/en_US/bikes/mountain-bikes/electric-mountain-bikes/marlin/c/B358/\" target=\"_blank\">TrekBikes.com</a></em></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/trek-marlin-plus-e-bike/\">Trek Marlin+ adds Bosch e-Bike Power to Popular Hardtail</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Tyler Benedict","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"8f653c70b57599d9bb9d41273f7565036323504deede095a5aa55841ab5b2a86","category":"Cycling"}